reviews.text: It’s amazing place to spend your day with kids. Lot and lots of rides and you need a day to ride each. Ofcourse they covered lot of rides for kids.

The staff were ok I suppose, there were big queues considering it was Monday especially for food. The place was fairly well maintained but it wasn’t very clean.

Just fine, nothing I’d go to again.

Full of enjoyable rides and great food but one thing I also loved is that there are many game stalls that are fun to play and win prizes on.Great family area and certain parts of the park for small children older basically for all the family.

Wrist bands are a fair price and throughout the summer they occasionally open until 10pm - which gives you linger on the rides due to the queues. 

Queues do go down quite fast, which is such advantage but I paid £15 for 4 hours in another car park: car parks become full so fast! - Get there early. 

However such a good place for all ages!
Always a joy with family, pleasure to walk on the beach
